esagt : mit filmen wie `` der soldat james ryan '' kann man diesen hier nicht vergleichen . `` der schmale grat '' ist eher ein `` ruhiger '' , nachdenklicher und dramatischer film der den zuschauer mehr zum nachdenken als zum `` adrenalinüberschuss '' anregt . ||| the `` special '' war film in `` the thin red line '' act of genius , many hollywood stars like george clooney , john cusack , nick nolte , sean penn , john travolta , and even more ! the film is a war epic of the `` superlative '' ! this film , however is different in many respects to his `` relatives '' such as `` saving private ryan . '' here , it is not just about historical battles , lots of blood and bombastic battles . certainly a part of war , however , the intensity here is somewhere else . the film is more drama than war films and plays in the 2nd world war ii on guadalcanal , solomon islands in the pacific ocean . the united states wants this island is occupied by the japanese to win back . the troops suffered heavy casualties - the soldiers were still alive are suffering from what they have done and seen and go bit by bit `` broken '' what distinguishes the movie mainly by the other is the relationship between the pristine beauty of nature with the ugly face of war rages out . the voice of a soldier ( james caviezel ) from the `` off '' makes it to the audience again and again deliberately . it is suggested here again and again to reflect on `` what really brings this evil in this beautiful world , '' and `` what good has it all . '' personally , i find the movie very well ! it 's like saying a melancholy very successful mix of drama and war movie ! with 170 minutes of film is an absolute excess length . if you will , however , enters an appearance to one here never gets boring . it runs through the whole film a depressed mood that draws the viewer fully under its spell . in some places , the film is very brutal . and when the gruesome side of war times it is shown this is not done playing dow